  "title": "How to scan a file share",
  "slug": "how-to-scan-a-file-share",
  "categorySlug": "data-sources",
  "html": "<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell \" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-1 dnd-section kb-article-row-0-padding\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell dnd-column\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-2 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-2\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-3 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h1 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">How to scan a file share</h1>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-4 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h2 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">We have three options depending on the location of the file share(s) that should be scanned.</h2>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-5 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_richtext_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_richtext_field\"><p>To scan a file share, it must be mounted on the DAMCS. If the DAMCS is delivered as a service, a VPN network must first be established.<br><br><strong>Direct Mount (only for on-premise installations)&nbsp;</strong><br><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" height=\"185\" style=\"height: auto; width: 230px;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=230&amp;height=185&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png\" width=\"230\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=115&amp;height=93&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 115w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=230&amp;height=185&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 230w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=345&amp;height=278&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 345w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=460&amp;height=370&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 460w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=575&amp;height=463&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 575w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png?width=690&amp;height=555&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-00-53-6360-AM.png 690w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 230px) 100vw, 230px\"></p>\n<p>We recommend using OnPremise DMCS installations to scan on-premise data exceeding 25TB</p>\n<p><strong>Point To Point VPN (default)</strong><br><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" height=\"192\" style=\"height: auto; width: 484px;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=484&amp;height=192&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png\" width=\"484\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=242&amp;height=96&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 242w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=484&amp;height=192&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 484w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=726&amp;height=288&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 726w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=968&amp;height=384&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 968w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=1210&amp;height=480&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 1210w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png?width=1452&amp;height=576&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-02-19-2985-AM.png 1452w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 484px) 100vw, 484px\"></p>\n<p>This is the recommended setup for under 25 TB of data with fewer than three million files.&nbsp; The VPN service is included in the default hybrid license. Please refer to the Point-to-Point <a href=\"//support.dataandmore.com/knowledge/onpremise-data\" rel=\"noopener\">VPN here</a>:</p>\n<p><br><strong>Site 2 Site VPN&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" height=\"183\" style=\"height: auto; width: 472px;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=472&amp;height=183&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png\" width=\"472\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=236&amp;height=92&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 236w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=472&amp;height=183&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 472w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=708&amp;height=275&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 708w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=944&amp;height=366&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 944w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=1180&amp;height=458&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 1180w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png?width=1416&amp;height=549&amp;name=image-png-May-02-2025-09-01-38-5967-AM.png 1416w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 472px) 100vw, 472px\"></p>\n<p>We recommend using site-to-site connections when serving more than three on-premises sources. Please be aware that site-to-site connections require a site-to-site license or a custom security framework. Currently, a 4.000 DKK a month license.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Please refer to the Site-to-Site <a href=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/en/knowledge/site-2-site-vpn-ipsec\" rel=\"noopener\">VPN here</a>:</p>\n<h3>How to mount the file-share - when the connections is established</h3>\n<div class=\"hs-callout-type-note\" data-hs-callout-type=\"note\">\n<p>Please provide Data &amp; More with:</p>\n<p>- IP or domain for the fileshare</p>\n<p>- AD user with read/write permissions</p>\n<p>- Make sure that the file share is visible from the toolbox</p>\n</div>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; table-layout: fixed; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border: 1px solid #99acc2;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>In general, please do not use @. Do not use&nbsp; “da@ju” as a user - but rather “daju55”. Also, when providing the users, please specify any configuration they may need for access. eg.:</p>\n<br>\n<p>VPN login: client_domain\\daju</p>\n<p>Windows login: daju55</p>\n<p>Exchange login: daju@client_domain.xxx</p>\n<br>\n<p>For password min 8 characters and do not use #, &amp;, /&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>AD</em></strong><strong> user for the Data Compliance Server to access file shares</strong></p>\n<p>In order to access file shares, the Data Compliance Server needs a unique AD user that has R/W permissions to all the data that the Server should analyze.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The password for the AD user should be static (not changed while we run our tool)&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Notice:</span> One of the typical client-side errors we encounter during set-up, is AD users who do not have the rights to read the data the Compliance Server should scan.<br><br></p>\n<p>When the Data Compliance Server can access the file share, it must be mounted directly as a drive on the D&amp;M Server using smba or other relevant protocols.</p>\n<p>The command needed to mount the file share on the Compliance server:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">mount -t cifs -o username=username,password=password //server-name/sharename /mountpoint</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The:&nbsp; /var&nbsp; directory should be min 500 GB on the Data Compliance Server according to the specs for the related set-up</p>\n<div class=\"hs-callout-type-note\" data-hs-callout-type=\"note\">\n<p>Please notice that codes for mounting SAN may vary. Also, make sure that the toolbox has the rights to mount the relevant files-share</p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div>\n</div>",
  "sourceUrl": "https://support.dataandmore.com/en/knowledge/how-to-scan-a-file-share"
}